        "content": "<p>Instead of doing this and hardcoding the string</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">expect</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">parsePartial</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">chompUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">'\\</span><span class=\"nv\">n'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">ParsingFailure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"character not found\"</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Maybe we could permit this? Or is there a better way?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nv\">expect</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">parsePartial</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">chompUntil</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">'\\</span><span class=\"nv\">n'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">==</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Err</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">ParsingFailure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"></span>\n</code></pre></div>",
